&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Barts Health NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Royal London Hospital- Neonatal Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locum Consultant in Paediatric Critical Care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(10 PAs)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are inviting applications to recruit a consultant in Paediatric Critical care. The successful candidate will be joining a pro-active team with an excellent clinical reputation in providing Paediatric Critical care to critically ill and injured children in North East London&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for applicants who can lead and develop innovative models of care which benefit the children and their families. We anticipate that the successful applicants will be part of a strong team and complement the existing team in delivering high quality care to critically ill or injured children..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If successful you will be employed by Barts Health NHS Trust and will be based at The Royal London Hospital, working 10 programmed activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal discussions and enquiries please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Simona Lampariello, Clinical Lead for PCCU (s.lampariello@nhs.net)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Vadivelam Murthy, Clinical Director for Specialist Paediatrics (v.murthy@nhs.net)&lt;/p&gt;
